cent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I came across the official documentation regarding the usage of the Jackson XML module on Android, which mentions the incompatibility due to the Stax API being unavailable on the platform. It also suggests that workarounds are required to use the module effectively on Android.\n\nHowever after following the provided dependencies for jackson-dataformat-xml, woodstox-core, and stax-api\n```\nimplementation 'com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat:jackson-dataformat-xml:2.18.2'\nimplementation 'com.fasterxml.woodstox:woodstox-core:7.1.0'\nimplementation 'javax.xml.stream:stax-api:1.0-2'\n```\n\nI found that the setup works without requiring any additional workarounds as mentioned in document.\nI believe this is working since version 2.15 of the Jackson XML lib. As per this [comment](https://stackoverflow.com/a/77218266/28834122) \n\nBased on this, I suggest updating the documentation to state that the mentioned dependencies are sufficient for integrating Jackson XML on Android without requiring additional workarounds.\n\n","closed_by":{"login":"cowtowncoder","id":55065,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1MDY1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/55065?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder","html_url":"https://github.com/cowtowncoder","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/cowtowncoder/events{/privacy}","re